The government is set to start installing digital migration television decoders or Set-Top-Boxes as they are more commonly known in the area.Minister of Communications Ms Faith Muthambi will visit the community on Tuesday as part of the government s broadcasting digital migration public awareness campaign.The Department of Communications is working together with the South African Post Office to reach communities and to distribute these fully subsidised television decoders. As part of its public awareness campaigns the Department has embarked on door to door visits.To qualify for the government-subsidised decoders households must earn less than R3 200 per month.